{
  "texts": [
    "While non-specialized digital twins may not allow individual patient precision, the approach could still increase precision for specific cohorts within the whole population.",
    "For diseases with more circumscribed features, however, specialized digital twins might offer precise intervention strategies and outcome predictions that could perform as well or better than those based on organoids.",
    "Another remarkable advantage of digital twins is that they allow a scenario-based modeling approach for actionable interventions-akin to strategies routinely used in epidemic modeling for policy decisionmaking 147 -that enhances their applicability and safety in clinical settings.",
    "This method avoids the standard pitfalls of an oracle-like predictive model by allowing for exploration via direct simulation of multiple clinical scenarios, thereby providing a robust tool for decision support in personalized medicine.",
    "It requires the crucial integration of massive data sets about disease or treatment progressions."
  ]
}